events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young and the Atlanta Hawks knew the Los Angeles Lakers would be a bit weary after playing 24 hours earlier in Houston.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 26 points, Hawks hand Lakers another double-digit defeat, 138-122

headlines.description: — The Celtics have won plenty of games this season by overpowering teams with their offense.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 30, comes up with late blocks as Celtics hold off Pacers 129-124

events.name: Utah Jazz at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson believed the New York Knicks were headed in the right direction when the calendar turned to 2024.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks win eighth straight, finish January 14-2 by beating Jazz 118-103

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 24, Bruce Brown added 19 points and seven rebounds and the Toronto Raptors snapped a season-high five-game losing streak with a 118-107 win over the Chicago Bulls on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gary Trent Jr. scores 24 to lead Raptors to 118-107 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Since Draymond Green returned from his second suspension of the season, the Golden State Warriors have begun looking like their balanced, ball-sharing selves again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 37 as Warriors beat 76ers 119-107
